### API Requests Helper File for Java Scheduler Middleware
# Use these requests to test the middleware locally.
# Default Dev API Key: default-dev-key

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@apiKey = default-dev-key

### 1. Test Generate Schedule (Simulation Mode - SUCCESS)
# In simulation mode, this generates a fully compliant schedule.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/schedule/generate
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-KEY: {{apiKey}}

{
  "prompt": "Schedule shifts for upcoming week"
}


### 2. Test Generate Schedule (Simulation Mode - WITH COMPLIANCE FAILURES)
# Sending the keyword "fail" or "violation" triggers mock compliance failures (Estonian labor law checks).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/schedule/generate
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-KEY: {{apiKey}}

{
  "prompt": "Schedule shifts, but make Tom fail validation to test rules"
}


### 3. Test Generate Schedule (Unauthorized Request - NO API KEY)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/schedule/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Schedule standard week"
}


### 4. Test Commit Schedule (Draft to Bubble database)
# Replace user names and times with actual records for testing.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/schedule/commit
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-KEY: {{apiKey}}

[
  {
    "Assigned User": "Tom",
    "Time - Start Time": "2026-06-29T08:00:00Z",
    "Time - End Time": "2026-06-29T16:00:00Z",
    "notes": "Committed standard day shift"
  },
  {
    "Assigned User": "Lily",
    "Time - Start Time": "2026-06-30T22:00:00Z",
    "Time - End Time": "2026-07-01T06:00:00Z",
    "notes": "Committed night shift"
  }
]
